  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      To conduct a quantitative survey to measure knowledge about Human papillomavirus (HPV) and
      cervical cancer, and HPV vaccine acceptability among parents of rural adolescent girls in
      Mysore District, India.

      Hypothesis: General knowledge and attitudes about the severity and treat ability of cancer
      will predict acceptability of HPV vaccination among parents of rural adolescent girls in
      Mysore, India.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
